Steaming Cup of Coffee

 
 
 

Project Loom with Ron Pressler and Alan Bateman  

Project Loom's mission is to make it easier to write, debug, profile and maintain concurrent applications meeting today's requirements. Check the video to get familiar with its concepts and how to adopt lightweight concurrency.

 
 
 

Time To Upgrade

 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

WildFly 14 is Released! Now With Full EE 8 and Some MicroProfile Support 

WildFly 14 is out! It is Java EE8 Certified and comes with MicroProfile support, High Performance Connection Pool and Mod-Cluster Multiplicity. For full release notes check this link. 

 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

SLF4J 1.8 Has Been Modularized 

In the 1.8.x series, SLF4J has been modularized per JPMS/Jigsaw specification. Moreover, slf4j-api now relies on the ServiceLoader mechanism to find its logging backend. ServiceLoader is available in Java 6 and later.

 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

JUnit 5.3 

JUnit 5.3 has been released. It features Parallel test execution, output capture for System.out and System.err, new TestInstanceFactory extension API, custom test sources for dynamic tests and more.

 

There Is Always More to Learn

 
 
 

Polymorphism Using Generics in Java  

This article is for junior developers who do not want to copy-paste their code over and over again for different cases. Understanding the subtyping in java will help you build more flexible software architecture. Check it out!

 
 
 
 

I Believe in Java Modules 

It is happening — Vavr 1.0 will ship as a set of Java modules. In this article, you will explore some fundamental design decisions and the rationale for slicing Vavr into modules. A great example how to apply modularity in practice.

 
 
 
 
 
 
 

JEP Draft: Lazy Static Final Fields 

Do we need a finer grained class initialization in Java? The answer might be “yes” and there is a new draft approaching which will target better optimizations performed by the JVM at compile time. Read the full proposal to learn more.

 
 
 
 

How to Extract a Data-Rich Service From a Monolith 

When breaking monoliths into smaller services, the hardest part is actually breaking up the data that lives in the database of the monolith. To extract a data-rich service, it is useful to follow a series of steps which retain a single write-copy of the data at all times. 

 
 
 
 
 

3 Reasons Why People Write Insanely Bad Code 

Ever wondered why you see bad code... everywhere? There are a few reasons why this keeps happening. Having an insight into the reasons behind bad code might help you to reduce it in your project.

 
 
 
 

8 Useful But Not Well-Known Git Concepts 

These lesser-known Git tricks can help you solve problems that are not handled well by the GitHub and BitBucket GUIs. Read on to increase your productivity with Git.

 
 
 
 
 
 

Hibernate Tips: Map 1 Entity Attribute to 2 Columns 

You have a legacy database that you don’t want to change. It stores a date and a timestamp in 2 separate columns. How can you map it to 1 entity attribute? Check out the article for the full solution with Hibernate.

User Impersonation With Spring Security 

User impersonation is very useful when testing permissions and content that only specific users can see. This guide walks through the process of creating an user impersonation from super / admin users with Spring Security.

 
 
 
 
 

JUnit 5 – Dynamic Tests 

With JUnit 5’s dynamic tests it is possible to define fully fledged test cases at run time. This way, tests can be created from parameters, external data sources, or simple lambda expressions. Check the article to see how this fixes a long-standing weakness of JUnit 4.

 
 
 
 
 
 

Jackson JSON Tutorial 

This tutorial illustrates the most common Jackson 2 tasks, problems and solutions while marshalling and unmarshalling JSON. You will learn how to serialize and deserialize in order to map Java Entities and JSON Strings in order to reach the outcome you’re aiming for. 

 
 
 
 
 
 

HTTPS Security Best Practices 

The single most important tip regarding HTTPS is to use it. But there are still many pitfalls you need to avoid. With this article you will discover what are some of the best practices and advices that will make your application more secure and trustworthy.
